---++ Tim Cartwright - Software

Since 10 February 2016.

---+++ Enterprise Linux 7

Visible progress continues to be very slow on finishing support for Java software on EL&amp;nbsp;7, primarily due to technical difficulty and effort (i.e., developers need to get other things done, too). Since February, we:

   * Made a solid !BeStMan testbed on !FermiCloud EL&amp;nbsp;6 and EL&amp;nbsp;7 to help with debugging and prototyping
   * Identified and fixed a simple packaging mistake for !BeStMan that resulted in obscure runtime failures
   * Are now investigating what it would take to change !BeStMan and GUMS to use VOMS API Java v3 (from v2) at least for EL&amp;nbsp;7

There are sites (Nebraska, Oklahoma, others?) that are starting to set up EL&amp;nbsp;7 hosts. So far, so good (except for Java parts, of course). But see below about SELinux. Also see “Concerns”, below, for more thoughts about Java and our future.

---+++ SELinux

With the move to EL&amp;nbsp;7, we will need to provide support for SELinux, which is a new feature for the OSG software stack&amp;nbsp;&amp;mdash; we have long advised sites to disable SELinux on OSG hosts. The Software team is just getting its head around this task, but it turns out that Patrick Calhoun at Oklahoma is an SELinux guru and created many of the necessary rules for OSG software at their site. He is sharing his results and configuration, and they will provide an excellent start toward official OSG support. Also, the HTCondor developers are working on SELinux support. I expect this to be a significant project in Q4 and perhaps beyond.

---+++ HTCondor-CE

HTCondor-CE continues to take a fairly low and steady amount of Software effort, as appropriate for its age and increasingly widespread deployment. Most development is driven by specific site needs.

   * Improved LSF, PBS, and SGE support
   * Add some attributes for Gratia reporting
   * Helping with HTCondor-CE-Bosco as requested (which is not much so far)
   * See below for more detailed notes on support

---+++ !StashCache and CVMFS-over-StashCache

We help with these broader projects as requested, but there has been relatively little Software involvement.

---+++ Releases

Reminder: OSG 3.2 has been deprecated since February and hence receives only critical updates (plus all CA certificate and VO client data updates, at least one of which occurs in nearly every release). The End-Of-Life date for OSG 3.2 and support for EL&amp;nbsp;5 is August 2016.

---+++ Other software updates

For users:
   * Gratia probes: We investigated and helped fix a problem with the HTCondor-CE probe that was affecting an increasing number of sites
   * Miscellaneous: !GlideinWMS, GUMS, Hadoop (newer patch level), HTCondor (8.4, 8.5), OSG CA certificates updater, OSG PKI tools, VO client data and CA certificates as needed, !XRootD

Internal:
