---+++ Concerns

   * Last (fiscal) year, the Technology Area leads (Brian B., Tim T., and I) tried to meet quarterly to review plans and the WBS. I found it helpful to set aside time for this kind of bigger-picture review, but we have not done any reviews this year.

   * Long-term sustainability of our big Java software components:
      * !BeStMan: Brian B. would like to drop it from OSG 3.4, which would be helpful. But is there a roadmap for making that happen?
      * VOMS Admin: We are trying to shift VOMS (and hence VOMS Admin) to hosted installations instead of site- or VO-operated installations. Waiting for dust to settle on CA transition, I think.
      * GUMS: We are going to live with this one for now. Many current issues lie with security libraries, and we may be able to shift to newer, externally maintained ones down the road.

   * There is still no policy or procedure for using the GOC Yum software repository

